AndroidiOS <p>In order to use the RFID feature, the user must give the NFC permission in runtime, otherwise it won't work. We already handle the permission check and added to the manifest the following: <pre><code>&lt;uses-permission android:name="android.permission.NFC" /&gt;
</code></pre> So when using the RFID feature, the user will be prompted to concede the permission if it hadn't already.</p> <p>Step 1: Add Near Field Communication Tag Reading under the Capabilities tab for the project’s target (or on your .entitlements file):</p> <pre><code>&lt;key&gt;com.apple.developer.nfc.readersession.formats&lt;/key&gt;
&lt;array&gt;
    &lt;string&gt;TAG&lt;/string&gt;
&lt;/array&gt;
</code></pre> <p></p> <p>Step 2:  Add the NFCReaderUsageDescription permission to your Info.plist file as its needed to access the NFC hardware:</p> <pre><code>&lt;key&gt;NFCReaderUsageDescription&lt;/key&gt;
&lt;string&gt;NFC tag to read NDEF messages&lt;/string&gt;
</code></pre> <p>Step 3: Declare <code>com.apple.developer.nfc.readersession.iso7816.select-identifiers</code> a list of application identifiers that the app must be able to read according to ISO7816:</p> <pre><code>&lt;key&gt;com.apple.developer.nfc.readersession.iso7816.select-identifiers&lt;/key&gt;
&lt;array&gt;
    &lt;string&gt;A0000002471001&lt;/string&gt;
    &lt;string&gt;E80704007F00070302&lt;/string&gt;
    &lt;string&gt;A000000167455349474E&lt;/string&gt;
    &lt;string&gt;A0000002480100&lt;/string&gt;
    &lt;string&gt;A0000002480200&lt;/string&gt;
    &lt;string&gt;A0000002480300&lt;/string&gt;
    &lt;string&gt;A00000045645444C2D3031&lt;/string&gt;
    &lt;string&gt;A0000002471001&lt;/string&gt;
    &lt;string&gt;A0000002472001&lt;/string&gt;
    &lt;string&gt;00000000000000&lt;/string&gt;
    &lt;string&gt;63000000000001&lt;/string&gt;
    &lt;string&gt;D4100000030001&lt;/string&gt;
&lt;/array&gt;
</code></pre> <p></p>

